Basic Editing Shortcuts
Ctrl + C: Copy selected text.
Ctrl + X: Cut selected text.
Ctrl + V: Paste copied/cut text.
Ctrl + Z: Undo the last action.
Ctrl + Y: Redo the last undone action.
Ctrl + A: Select all text in the current document.
Ctrl + F: Open the Find dialog to search for text in the document.
Ctrl + H: Open the Replace dialog to replace text.
Navigation Shortcuts
Ctrl + G: Go to a specific line in the current document.
Ctrl + Tab: Switch between open documents.
Ctrl + - (Minus): Navigate to the previous location in the code.
Ctrl + Shift + - (Minus): Navigate to the next location in the code.
Ctrl + Shift + F: Search for a text string in all files in the solution.
Code Editing Shortcuts
Ctrl + K, Ctrl + D: Format the document.
Ctrl + K, Ctrl + C: Comment selected lines of code.
Ctrl + K, Ctrl + U: Uncomment selected lines of code.
F12: Go to the definition of a selected symbol (e.g., function, variable).
Ctrl + . (Period): Show the Quick Actions and Refactorings menu for the selected code.
Debugging Shortcuts
F5: Start debugging the application.
Shift + F5: Stop debugging.
Additional Shortcuts
Ctrl + Shift + B: Build the solution.
Ctrl + R, Ctrl + R: Rename the selected variable, method, or class.